\newlabel{fig:tolerance}{{12}{12}{Terminal-miss success rate as a function of tolerance, taken from the same $n=1000$ CR3BP-truth and SPICE-point-mass-truth baseline runs. Vertical guides mark the paper threshold ($10^{-3}\,\LU = 390$ km) and the tighter $10^{-4}\,\LU = 39$ km point used as the reality-check level}{figure.12}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {13}{\ignorespaces Attitude-noise sensitivity sweep, $n=1000$ trials per $\sigma _\text  {att}$ point. The left panel shows median and 95th-percentile terminal miss; the right panel shows the median Moon-center NIS and median NEES/3. The performance plateau extends to roughly $\sigma _\text  {att}=0.1$ deg before the filter becomes inconsistent and miss climbs steeply.}}{12}{figure.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:attitude}{{13}{12}{Attitude-noise sensitivity sweep, $n=1000$ trials per $\sigma _\text {att}$ point. The left panel shows median and 95th-percentile terminal miss; the right panel shows the median Moon-center NIS and median NEES/3. The performance plateau extends to roughly $\sigma _\text {att}=0.1$ deg before the filter becomes inconsistent and miss climbs steeply}{figure.13}{}}
